(90, 'Hannah Laurence', 'hlaurence@sonatype.com', '07900607614', 'ITSA', 'Nuremberg', NULL, '24', '2', 'United Kingdom', 'Hi, \r\nI was wondering if you could help me. \r\nI am currently going out to tender to source a new supplier for our booth build at IT-SA in Nuremberg in October. In the past we have used one supplier for all our events across Europe, however we are finding it a very expensive way of working and therefore I am looking for a German based organisation to help me with this. \r\n\r\nAt the moment we are currently going through a brand refresh so I can\'t provide you specific specification of what we would be looking for, but I wanted to share what we did last year at IT-SA you can get a feel for what we like and we would love to also hear your thoughts on some new ideas. \r\n\r\nWe have changed our position at IT-SA for 2024, so our booth will be slightly differently positioned. \r\n\r\nHall: 7\r\nStand number: 7-350\r\nFront breadth (in m): 6,00\r\nDepth (in m): 4,00\r\nTotal space (in m²): 24,00\r\nStand type: in-line stand (1 side open)\r\nColumn in the stand space: No\r\n\r\nAttached you can find our space position and I have also attached the full floor plan so you can see the whole space. \r\n\r\nSomethings to consider: \r\n- We love an outwards facing screen to do live demos \r\n- Keeping things open and inviting as much as possible\r\n- There is always one demo station, a meeting space and a cupboard for storage \r\n- We always have something fun in the booth. Last year we had a waffle station (from an outside vendor) and we had two branded beer taps with a space underneath the desk for 2 kegs. \r\n- Light up Sonatype logos \r\n- We love plants and green walls! \r\n\r\nAs soon as I have our new brand specs I will of course share these, but it would be great to hear your initial thoughts whilst we work on shortening a list of suppliers to take discussions further. \r\nThanks, \r\nHannah', NULL, NULL, 'Quotation Form', '/quotation-form/', '2.2