(558, 'Mardi Van Wyk', 'graphics@flownex.com', '0716218035', 'ASME Turbo Expo 2025', 'Memphis, Tennessee', NULL, '10x10_Booth', '1', 'South Africa', 'Hi there,\r\nAccording to the ASME Turbo Expo guidelines, the maximum height of 8ft (2.44m) is allowed only in the rear half of the booth space, with a 4ft (1.22m) height restriction for materials in the front section leading to the aisle.\r\n\r\nFor our booth mock-up, we’d like to have left and right walls at 2440mm high × 3000mm wide. The approval for these walls is currently in process, directly from Management @Kristin Barranger  at ASME.  In the meantime, could you provide a quote based on the attached isometric example? \r\n\r\nAdditionally, we’d like to include a fourth LED light next to the TV monitor, positioned to shine down onto the printed graphics on the wall.\r\nLooking forward to your quote on these specific items?\r\n BeMatrix Backwall, approx. 3048 mm (wide) x  2413 mm (height)\r\n with support for wall.\r\n BeMatrix Return Wall, approx.  3048 mm (wide) x  2413 mm (height)\r\nQty. (4) Rental LED Stem Lights\r\nReception Counter.  42” wide x 24” deep x 40” high, should be able to lock.\r\nQty. (1) SEG Fabric Graphic for Backwall - 3048 mm (wide) x  2413 mm (height)\r\nQty. (1) SEG Fabric Graphic for Returnwall - 3048 mm (wide) x  2413 mm (height)\r\nQty. (1) Reception Counter Graphic\r\nQty. (1) White Round Bar Table\r\nQty. (4) White Bar Stools \r\n10’x10’ rental grey carpet and pad\r\nQty. (1) 65” TV monitor with wall mounting bracket & HDMI\r\n\r\nBrochure Stand 2-3 shelving - no taller than 1 meter\r\n\r\nRound trip freight from production facility to Advance Warehouse - Travel Costs\r\n\r\nLabour for Build-up and Strike Installation: Monday, June 16, qty. (1) man x (8) hours ST Dismantle: Friday, June 20, qty. (1) man x (4) hours ST\r\n\r\nPlease let me know how your process will proceed. Also, if you have any additional suggestions or a catalog for brochure stands, bar stools, and tables to choose